Course I am.

25:24.520 --> 25:26.432
We're all on the same side, aren't we?

25:27.680 --> 25:29.319
You know where you're going, don't ya?

25:29.960 --> 25:31.076
Don't stray from the path.

25:32.960 --> 25:34.713
Can't be too careful round this way.

25:49.520 --> 25:50.976
You need to trust me, Michael.

25:51.000 --> 25:53.640
You're not going to London.
You and I are going back to Kiloran.

26:11.040 --> 26:12.633
The fuck!

26:14.720 --> 26:15.720
Shit!

26:23.520 --> 26:24.520
Fuck!

26:35.720 --> 26:37.200
Woah, woah, woah!

26:37.240 --> 26:39.152
Prom queen's got a gun.

26:50.440 --> 26:52.079
You're in no condition to be doing that.

26:52.480 --> 26:53.480
Keep moving.

26:54.400 --> 26:58.235
We can help ya.
- Yeah, yeah. I know how karma works.

26:58.880 --> 27:00.280
I burst a bunch of tyres

27:00.400 --> 27:02.676
and now mine's burst randomly
for no reason at all.

27:03.480 --> 27:06.200
I almost run you down
and now you want revenge.

27:06.440 --> 27:07.440
Au contraire.

27:08.360 --> 27:09.589
Au contraire, mademoiselle.

27:10.880 --> 27:15.352
You almost running us over blessed us
with a newfound appreciation for life.

27:15.800 --> 27:19.316
Ours, yours,
that little bundle you got in there...

27:20.200 --> 27:21.554
and changing your tyre

27:22.400 --> 27:24.232
would be the least we can do in return.

27:28.560 --> 27:29.560
Alright.

27:32.640 --> 27:33.960
Well, get out and change it then.

27:34.280 --> 27:36.272
Yep. Here we go.

27:36.440 --> 27:38.716
Keep your hands where I can see them.
- Jazz hands.

27:46.520 --> 27:48.056
Looks like... almost like a nail.

27:48.080 --> 27:49.280
That's close enough.
- Alright.

27:50.440 --> 27:52.320
Look, why don't you sit down
and let us do this?

27:52.360 --> 27:53.360
No.

27:53.760 --> 27:54.760
You want a massage?

27:57.160 --> 27:59.600
Look, I'd like to think I know
a little something about crazy.

27:59.640 --> 28:00.640
No shit.

28:00.920 --> 28:03.071
You're, what - 36, 37 weeks along?

28:05.400 --> 28:06.400
Thirty eight.

28:06.560 --> 28:08.597
Honey, you gotta get yourself to a hospital.

28:09.360 --> 28:10.430
I'm a doctor, trust me.

28:12.400 --> 28:14.000
People do natural birthing all the time.

28:14.440 --> 28:16.636
Yeah, not in moving cars.
- What's the alternative?

28:17.160 --> 28:18.640
Miss out on the race and stay here?

28:19.360 --> 28:23.070
Raise a child in a world
where there are monsters and curfews

28:23.120 --> 28:25.476
and people who will do anything to survive?

28:26.920 --> 28:28.115
I'd rather take the risk.

28:29.080 --> 28:31.390
Come with us, let us look after you.

28:32.240 --> 28:33.720
So the secret, Cheese...

28:33.840 --> 28:36.674
is you grab the shaft with both hands
and then you tickle the nuts.

28:36.760 --> 28:38.080
That way it stays on, you see.

28:38.720 --> 28:40.393
Why you gotta say things like that, man?

28:42.480 --> 28:43.480
All done.

28:44.200 --> 28:45.111
Well done, son.

28:45.160 --> 28:47.120
Watch out, man's coming through
on a wheelie ting.

28:50.320 --> 28:51.320
I'm doing this on my own.

28:52.520 --> 28:53.520
Come on, now.

28:54.160 --> 28:55.355
No matter who you are

28:55.880 --> 28:59.920
or what you do to live, thrive or survive

29:00.880 --> 29:02.553
there's some things...
- Oh!

29:02.600 --> 29:03.795
...that make us all the same.

29:04.920 --> 29:06.320
You. Me.

29:06.880 --> 29:08.678
Them. Everybody.

29:09.880 --> 29:12.475
<i>♪ Do, do, do, do-do, do, do, do ♪</i>

29:12.640 --> 29:14.791
<i>♪ Dun, dun, dun, dun-dun, dun ♪</i>

29:15.080 --> 29:19.120
<i>♪ Everybody needs somebody ♪</i>

29:19.720 --> 29:24.875
<i>♪ Everybody needs somebody to love ♪</i>

29:25.680 --> 29:27.194
<i>♪ Someone to love ♪</i>

29:29.920 --> 29:32.071
<i>♪ Someone to miss ♪
- ♪ Someone to miss ♪</i>

29:32.440 --> 29:34.591
<i>♪ Sugar to kiss ♪
- ♪ Sugar to kiss ♪</i>

29:34.680 --> 29:37.798
<i>♪ Cos I need you, you, you
In the morning ♪</i>

29:38.000 --> 29:40.390
<i>♪ You, you, you ♪
- ♪ When my heart's on fire ♪</i>

29:40.640 --> 29:43.394
<i>♪ You, you, you ♪
- ♪ Whoo! I need you, you, you... ♪</i>

29:54.880 --> 29:55.880
Ooh!

30:07.480 --> 30:08.800
I need to get after Michael.

30:09.400 --> 30:10.516
Manchester's rough.

30:10.560 --> 30:11.560
We're coming with you.

30:12.040 --> 30:13.110
Look, it's alright.

30:13.640 --> 30:16.075
Roman told us how important Michael is.

30:17.720 --> 30:19.200
I really appreciate your help

30:20.000 --> 30:21.195
but you've both got families.

30:21.240 --> 30:23.197
You should be concentrating on
winning the race

30:23.240 --> 30:24.390
not taking any more risks.

30:24.960 --> 30:26.553
Your sister died saving us.

30:28.720 --> 30:30.074
I don't forget stuff like that.

30:32.720 --> 30:34.393
It's what separates us from the mooks

30:36.920 --> 30:39.230
sacrifice, altruism and guts.

30:42.280 --> 30:46.320
We're all in this race
cos we wanna get out of this shit.

30:48.200 --> 30:50.920
What's the point in winning if we lose
everything that matters?

30:53.560 --> 30:54.789
From what Roman says

30:55.280 --> 30:58.671
saving Michael will stop another family
losing someone they love.

31:01.280 --> 31:04.159
I'd say that's a chance worth taking,
wouldn't you?

31:07.400 --> 31:08.675
But once we get Michael back

31:09.520 --> 31:10.556
the gloves are off again.

31:11.160 --> 31:12.310
Every team for themselves.

31:13.400 --> 31:14.400
Agreed?

31:16.400 --> 31:17.800
I wouldn't have it any other way.

31:21.520 --> 31:22.520
Thank you.

31:25.000 --> 31:26.354
Word of advice, junior...

31:26.880 --> 31:27.916
If you're a boy

31:28.880 --> 31:31.759
don't make the mistake of thinking
you can solve every girl's problems.

31:32.400 --> 31:36.235
And if you're a girl, don't expect a man
to fix everything for you.

31:37.760 --> 31:40.639
Wow. That is incredibly profound, y'know.

31:41.840 --> 31:43.752
Cos, like, even though I'm a boy

31:44.080 --> 31:46.640
I think maybe I do expect men
to fix things for me.

31:47.000 --> 31:49.310
Don't get me wrong,
I'm good with electrical things.

31:50.080 --> 31:52.879
But, like, plumbing,
I really struggle with that shit.

31:53.520 --> 31:56.274
And plants, anything to do
with plants actually, I don't like plants.

31:56.320 --> 31:57.959
What the fuck are you doing in my car?

32:00.200 --> 32:02.351
Thought maybe
I could be your birthing partner, innit.

32:03.440 --> 32:04.760
What do you know about birthing?

32:05.280 --> 32:07.590
Right, when the rumour of the mooks
first started, yeah

32:07.680 --> 32:09.637
my sister was eight months pregnant.

32:10.720 --> 32:14.430
I was stuck with her for three weeks, mans,
just the two of us, no escape.

32:17.520 --> 32:18.556
You delivered her baby?

32:18.720 --> 32:21.792
No, man, that's my sister!
I don't want to see all that.

32:22.280 --> 32:24.033
We just watched loads of <i>Call The Midwife.</i>

32:26.000 --> 32:28.993
Let me tell you this -
giving birth is actually a piece of piss.

32:29.040 --> 32:30.520
You ain't got nothing to worry about.

32:34.040 --> 32:35.360
This music is good, y'know.

32:36.080 --> 32:37.116
Very ambient.

32:38.920 --> 32:40.912
Very relaxing, actually. What is it?

32:43.720 --> 32:44.720
It's whale song.

32:46.080 --> 32:48.037
Whales...? Fishes can't sing.

32:49.120 --> 32:50.520
They're not fish. They're mammals.

32:51.920 --> 32:54.560
I never knew that.

32:55.320 --> 32:57.880
Here's me thinking
I was gonna help you out, innit. Haha!

33:01.440 --> 33:03.318
- Are you sure about this?
- Yeah.

33:04.520 --> 33:06.716
Whenever we had to move freight after dark

33:06.760 --> 33:09.320
it was always Officer Darby
who sorted it for us.

33:11.280 --> 33:12.280
Boss!

33:17.280 --> 33:18.280
Hi.

33:21.880 --> 33:23.314
Alright, Lou Lou.

33:24.360 --> 33:27.751
Aren't you supposed to be
representing us in the Wacky Races?

33:29.160 --> 33:30.594
Yeah. Detour.

33:31.200 --> 33:33.920
We need to get after that truck
you just let through.

33:34.040 --> 33:35.190
Yeah? Why's that then?

33:35.280 --> 33:36.960
It's got my friend Michael inside it.

33:37.040 --> 33:39.271
Is he sick or something?
- No.

33:39.720 --> 33:40.949
Then why would Brookeheath

33:41.040 --> 33:43.600
want to airlift him out of here
in the middle of the night?

33:43.640 --> 33:45.856
Airlift him from where?
- Why the fuck should I tell you?

33:45.880 --> 33:48.315
Come on, Darby.
- Don't "come on, Darby" me.

33:49.720 --> 33:51.200
You're asking me to break the curfew.

33:57.960 --> 34:00.111
I should arrest you just for being out here.

34:02.040 --> 34:03.040
Go on then.

34:10.080 --> 34:11.594
Yeah, you're not going to, are you?

34:12.000 --> 34:14.310
Because if you were going to,
you'd have done it already

34:14.360 --> 34:15.360
so stop dicking about.

34:17.760 --> 34:18.989
Listen, I get it, right?

34:19.800 --> 34:21.120
I'm a businesswoman

34:21.400 --> 34:23.277
I know you're holding out for a price

34:24.000 --> 34:25.116
so how about this?

34:25.440 --> 34:27.556
You said they're being airlifted
out of here, right?

34:28.199 --> 34:30.157
Yeah.
- Right. You radio ahead.

34:30.520 --> 34:33.513
You tell 'em there's a security breach
and they need to redirect

34:34.000 --> 34:35.036
via my factory.

34:36.199 --> 34:38.795
Then you let us through,
and when we've done what we need to

34:39.239 --> 34:40.594
you get to keep the factory.

34:46.199 --> 34:48.396
Sue and I bought it when Salford
was on its arse.

34:50.199 --> 34:52.840
The machinery alone's worth
a few hundred thousand now.

34:56.920 --> 34:58.559
We're racing to win or we die trying.

34:59.400 --> 35:00.959
Either way, we're not coming back.

35:10.720 --> 35:12.200
Welcome to Manchester.

35:12.520 --> 35:13.880
Know where you're going, don't ya?

35:48.360 --> 35:50.240
- Everyone know what they're doing?
- Yeah.

35:50.560 --> 35:53.917
We're picking a fight with a private security
psycho and a couple of dirty cops.

35:54.760 --> 35:56.194
Yeah, well, we've got the numbers

35:57.320 --> 35:58.595
and we're on home turf.

35:59.120 --> 36:00.793
Here, take my spare.

36:06.240 --> 36:07.240
Let's do this.

36:13.720 --> 36:14.720
We're here.

36:15.480 --> 36:16.480
Get out of the truck.

36:25.200 --> 36:26.360
Is there a problem?

36:26.640 --> 36:27.640
Where's the helicopter?

36:29.080 --> 36:30.400
That's what I wanna know.

36:31.680 --> 36:32.875
Get your boss on the radio.

36:36.200 --> 36:37.200
Something wrong?

36:41.160 --> 36:42.389
You redirected us.

36:42.480 --> 36:44.551
The chopper was supposed to be here
when we arrived.

36:45.120 --> 36:46.120
Where is it?

36:46.960 --> 36:49.236
<i>Do I sound like
one of those fellas landing planes</i>

36:49.280 --> 36:50.634
<i>with a couple of ping pong bats?</i>

36:50.760 --> 36:51.955
Put your weapons down.

36:59.360 --> 37:00.360
Ladies first.

37:12.840 --> 37:15.121
OK, so this would qualify
as a "Mexican stand-off".

37:15.480 --> 37:17.960
The balance of powers between the two sides
appear to be equal.

37:22.280 --> 37:24.556
Well, that obviously changes things.

37:25.440 --> 37:27.193
Michael cannot go back to Brookeheath.

37:28.240 --> 37:30.550
Kaye, I'm on your side.

37:30.840 --> 37:32.718
You should stick to the microscope.

37:36.960 --> 37:38.400
That means we're back where we were.

37:39.120 --> 37:40.440
Roman, stop talking.

37:40.960 --> 37:41.960
OK.

37:46.200 --> 37:47.634
Someone needs to get the keys.

37:49.200 --> 37:50.200
The keys...?

37:54.360 --> 37:56.875
Oh, right. OK.

38:03.440 --> 38:04.680
I don't care who else you shoot

38:05.680 --> 38:07.319
but you touch my son and I'll kill you.

38:30.960 --> 38:32.189
Hey.
- Hey.

38:46.120 --> 38:47.120
You alright?

38:48.080 --> 38:49.080
Yeah.

38:52.560 --> 38:54.756
You two head for the cars. We'll follow on.

38:57.200 --> 38:58.200
And if he follows?

39:00.080 --> 39:01.080
He won't.

39:02.600 --> 39:04.159
Is there room for a little one?

39:05.120 --> 39:08.238
This is my factory now.
Ain't that right, Lou Lou?

39:10.320 --> 39:12.915
Doesn't mean you have to behave like a dick.

39:14.160 --> 39:15.992
Now, now. Deal's a deal.

39:16.600 --> 39:19.069
And that means everything in here
belongs to me

39:19.960 --> 39:21.030
including him.

39:22.320 --> 39:24.710
And I'm guessing you've gotta be worth
a few quid

39:24.760 --> 39:27.036
for everyone to be going to this much
trouble over you.

39:28.080 --> 39:32.154
So why don't you all
just put down your guns

39:32.720 --> 39:34.040
leave him with me...

39:34.400 --> 39:36.232
and piss off out

39:37.400 --> 39:38.800
or the kid gets it.

39:40.200 --> 39:41.236
We've got to do it, Kaye.

39:41.480 --> 39:42.709
Absolutely not.

39:43.600 --> 39:46.240
Michael is a valuable medical asset.
- I don't care!

39:47.400 --> 39:48.436
Hold on, Mum.

39:48.480 --> 39:51.439
If everyone put down their guns
then Robocop gets a free shot at Kaye

39:51.720 --> 39:54.280
and anyone else he wants.
- Which one's Robocop?

39:57.240 --> 39:59.080
Why don't we just take him out
of the equation?

39:59.520 --> 40:01.876
- But then we lose Michael to Darby.
- Fuck Michael.

40:03.320 --> 40:04.320
Put down your guns.

40:06.480 --> 40:08.392
Can everyone just put down your guns?

40:12.560 --> 40:13.560
Put down your guns!

40:15.320 --> 40:17.516
- I'm not that important, Mum.
- Yes, you are!

40:18.800 --> 40:20.951
Everyone, just put down your guns.

40:21.480 --> 40:22.516
Woah, woah, woah!

40:24.480 --> 40:25.480
What are you doing?

40:25.800 --> 40:26.960
I'm what this is all about...

40:28.520 --> 40:29.520
right?

40:30.840 --> 40:32.274
All of you are here because of me.

40:33.840 --> 40:35.957
So how about we take me out of the equation?

40:36.560 --> 40:39.837
You can all just get back to the job -
the race

40:41.280 --> 40:42.475
and get on with your lives.

40:42.880 --> 40:44.234
Michael, you're too important.

40:44.920 --> 40:46.760
With what we know now,
we could find a vaccine.

40:48.560 --> 40:49.640
So you've got all you need.

40:50.040 --> 40:52.635
No, I need to run a whole new set of tests
on your immune system.

40:53.200 --> 40:54.236
You're a smart guy.

40:55.560 --> 40:56.560
You'll figure it out.

40:57.240 --> 40:58.240
No.

41:00.960 --> 41:01.960
No.

41:03.000 --> 41:05.879
I can't keep letting people die
because of me.

41:07.760 --> 41:08.760
The world needs you.

41:10.480 --> 41:11.480
I need you.

41:13.520 --> 41:14.520
That's why we're here.

41:17.600 --> 41:18.829
And to save the world.

41:21.160 --> 41:22.160
Sixty-forty.

41:31.960 --> 41:32.960
Move, Roman.

41:33.440 --> 41:34.440
Move.

41:41.640 --> 41:44.758
Well, that load of bollocks
puts us back to square one, doesn't it?

41:46.040 --> 41:48.157
Except it doesn't, cos I miscalculated.

41:48.600 --> 41:50.034
Stop moving your bonce.

41:51.640 --> 41:52.756
Get down!

42:17.800 --> 42:18.800
Is he dead?

42:30.960 --> 42:31.960
Yeah.

42:37.920 --> 42:38.920
Nice shooting!

42:41.480 --> 42:42.516
Meg, you alright?

42:42.720 --> 42:44.996
I think I might need
some medical assistance...

42:45.880 --> 42:46.880
Come here.

42:47.760 --> 42:49.319
You OK?

42:52.200 --> 42:54.078
It's the strangest feeling.

42:55.520 --> 42:58.399
It's like falling backwards in slow motion...

42:59.360 --> 43:00.680
Let's get him to the ambulance.

43:04.320 --> 43:07.040
Cleaner's gonna have the right hump
when she comes in in the morning.

43:08.640 --> 43:11.030
Alright, let's get racing.

